  #' Libraries files.
  libraries:
    #' Structure organism pairs libraries.
    sop:
      #' Merged structure organism pairs library.
      merged:
        #' Organisms libraries.
        organisms:
          #' Organisms taxonomies.
          taxonomies:
            #' OTT organisms taxonomy. STRING
            ott: data/interim/libraries/sop/merged/organisms/taxonomies/ott.tsv.gz

#' Names of the different variables in the input files.
names:
  #' The file(s) extension is present in the sample name. BOOLEAN
  extension: yes

  #' Name of "feature IDs" variable in the input. STRING
  features: row ID

  #' Name of "filename" variable in the input. STRING
  filename: filename

  #' Name of the "taxon name" variable in the input. STRING
  taxon: ATTRIBUTE_species

#' Organisms related parameters.
organisms:
  #' Number of organisms to keep per feature. INTEGER
  candidates: 1

  #' OPTIONAL. If your experiment contains a single taxon, its scientific name.
  #' Else, you will need to provide a metadata file above.
  #' If you provide both, this one will have priority.
  #' Example: "Homo sapiens". STRING
  taxon: ~

name: params/default/weight_annotations.yaml
content:
---
#' Annotations related parameters.
annotations:
  #' Number of candidates to keep per feature.
  candidates:
    #' Number of final candidates. INTEGER
    final: 3

  #' Erase MS2 results and keep MS1 only. BOOLEAN
  ms1only: no

  #' Thresholds related parameters.
  thresholds:
    #' Minimal consistency score (chemical) to consider a class. FLOAT
    consistency: 0.0

    #' MS1 annotation related parameters.
    ms1:
      #' Minimal biological score to keep MS1 only annotation. FLOAT
      biological: 0.0

      #' Minimal chemical score to keep MS1 only annotation. FLOAT
      chemical: 0.0

      #' Condition to be used to retain candidates.
      #' Must be "OR" or "AND".
      #' Example: Minimum 0.3 biological AND 0.3 chemical. STRING
      condition: OR

#' Files.
files:
  #' Pattern to identify the files. STRING
  pattern: example

  #' Annotations files.
  annotations:
    #' List of filtered annotations. STRING
    filtered:
      - data/interim/annotations/example_annotationsFiltered.tsv.gz

    #' List of prepared annotations.
    prepared:
      #' List of prepared canopus annotations. STRING
      canopus: data/interim/annotations/example_canopusPrepared.tsv.gz

      #' List of prepared formula annotations. STRING
      formula: data/interim/annotations/example_formulaPrepared.tsv.gz

    #' Final results file. STRING
    processed: annotations.tsv

  #' Libraries files.
  libraries:
    #' Structure organism pairs libraries.
    sop:
      #' Merged structure organism pairs library.
      merged:
        #' Merged structure organism pairs library keys. STRING
        keys: data/interim/libraries/sop/merged/keys.tsv.gz

        #' Organisms libraries.
        organisms:
          #' Organisms taxonomies.
          taxonomies:
            #' OTT organisms taxonomy. STRING
            ott: data/interim/libraries/sop/merged/organisms/taxonomies/ott.tsv.gz

        #' Structures libraries.
        structures:
          #' Structures stereo. STRING
          stereo: data/interim/libraries/sop/merged/structures/stereo.tsv.gz

  #' Networks files.
  networks:
    #' Spectral networks files.
    spectral:
      #' Components files.
      components:
        #' Prepared edges file. STRING
        prepared: data/interim/features/example_componentsPrepared.tsv

      #' Edges files.
      edges:
        #' Prepared edges file. STRING
        prepared: data/interim/features/example_edges.tsv

  #' Metadata files.
  metadata:
    #' Taxonomically informed features file. STRING
    prepared: data/interim/taxa/example_taxed.tsv.gz

#' Weights to apply to each part of the final score.
weights:
  #' Global weights.
  global:
    #' Weight for the biological part. FLOAT
    biological: 0.500

    #' Weight for the chemical part. FLOAT
    chemical: 0.166

    #' Weight for the spectral part. FLOAT
    spectral: 0.333

  #' Weights for the biological part.
  biological:
    #' Score for a biological domain match. FLOAT
    domain: 0.10

    #' Score for a biological kingdom match. FLOAT
    kingdom: 0.20

    #' Score for a biological phylum match. FLOAT
    phylum: 0.30

    #' Score for a biological class match. FLOAT
    class: 0.40

    #' Score for a biological order match. FLOAT
    order: 0.50

    #' Score for a biological infraorder match. FLOAT
    infraorder: 0.55

    #' Score for a biological family match. FLOAT
    family: 0.60

    #' Score for a biological subfamily match. FLOAT
    subfamily: 0.65

    #' Score for a biological tribe match. FLOAT
    tribe: 0.70

    #' Score for a biological subtribe match. FLOAT
    subtribe: 0.75

    #' Score for a biological genus match. FLOAT
    genus: 0.80

    #' Score for a biological subgenus match. FLOAT
    subgenus: 0.85

    #' Score for a biological species match. FLOAT
    species: 0.90

    #' Score for a biological subspecies match. FLOAT
    subspecies: 0.95

    #' Score for a biological variety match. FLOAT
    variety: 1.00

  #' Weights for the chemical part.
  chemical:
    #' Score for a classyfire match.
    cla:
      #' Score for a chemical kingdom match. FLOAT
      kingdom: 0.25

      #' Score for a chemical superclass match. FLOAT
      superclass: 0.50

      #' Score for a chemical class match. FLOAT
      class: 0.75

      #' Score for a chemical parent match. FLOAT
      parent: 1.00

    #' Score for a NPClassifier match.
    npc:
      #' Score for a chemical kingdom match. FLOAT
      pathway: 0.333

      #' Score for a chemical superclass match. FLOAT
      superclass: 0.666

      #' Score for a chemical class match. FLOAT
      class: 1.000

#' Options.
options:
  #' Report compounds names. Can be very large. BOOLEAN
  compounds_names: no

  #' Do not use it. BOOLEAN
  force: no

  #' Filter high confidence candidates only. BOOLEAN
  high_confidence: yes

  #' Remove ties. BOOLEAN
  remove_ties: no

  #' Summarise results to one row per feature. BOOLEAN
  summarise: no

name: params/prepare_params.yaml
content:
---
files:
  #' The pattern identifying your whole job. You can put whatever you want. STRING
  pattern: example
  features:
    #' The path to the file containing your features' intensities.
    #' Can be generated by MZMine3 or SLAW. STRING
    raw: data/source/example_features.csv
  metadata:
    #' The path to the file containing your metadata.
    #' Must be formatted accordingly.
    #' If your experiment contains a single taxon, you can provide it below instead. STRING
    raw: data/source/example_metadata.tsv
  spectral:
    #' The path to the file containing your features' spectra.
    #' Can contain MS1 and/or MS2 spectra. STRING
    raw: data/source/example_spectra.mgf
  #' Annotations files.
  annotations:
    raw:
      #' Directory containing the sirius annotations. STRING
      sirius: data/interim/annotations/example_sirius.zip
ms:
  #' The polarity used. Must be either "pos" or "neg". STRING
  polarity: pos
organisms:
  #' OPTIONAL. If your experiment contains a single taxon, its scientific name.
  #' Else, you will need to provide a metadata file above.
  #' If you provide both, this one will have priority.
  #' Example: "Homo sapiens". STRING
  taxon: ~
options:
  #' Filter high confidence candidates only. BOOLEAN
  high_confidence: yes
  #' Do you want to summarize all candidates per feature to a single row? BOOLEAN
  summarise: no

name: params/prepare_params_advanced.yaml
content:
---
#' Annotations related parameters.
annotations:
  #' Number of candidates to keep per feature.
  candidates:
    #' Number of final candidates. INTEGER
    final: 3

  #' Erase MS2 results and keep MS1 only. BOOLEAN
  ms1only: no

  #' Perform approximative matching without precursor matching? BOOLEAN
  ms2approx: no

  #' Thresholds related parameters.
  thresholds:
    #' Minimal consistency score (chemical) to consider a class. FLOAT
    consistency: 0.0

    #' MS1 annotation related parameters.
    ms1:
      #' Minimal biological score to keep MS1 only annotation. FLOAT
      biological: 0.0

      #' Minimal chemical score to keep MS1 only annotation. FLOAT
      chemical: 0.0

      #' Condition to be used to retain candidates.
      #' Must be "OR" or "AND".
      #' Example: Minimum 0.3 biological AND 0.3 chemical. STRING
      condition: OR

    #' MS2 annotation related parameters.
    ms2:
      #' For similarity.
      similarity:
        #' For annotation. FLOAT
        annotation: 0.0

        #' For edges. FLOAT
        edges: 0.7

#' Files.
files:
  #' Pattern to identify the files. STRING
  pattern: example

  #' Annotations files.
  annotations:
    #' Raw annotations files.
    raw:
      #' List of spectral matching annotations.
      spectral:
        #' GNPS spectral matching annotations. STRING
        gnps: data/interim/annotations/example_gnps.tsv

        #' Spectral spectral matching annotations. STRING
        spectral: data/interim/annotations/example_spectralMatches.tsv.gz

      #' Directory containing the sirius annotations. STRING
      sirius: data/interim/annotations/example_sirius

    #' List of filtered annotations. STRING
    filtered: data/interim/annotations/example_annotationsFiltered.tsv.gz

    #' List of prepared annotations.
    prepared:
      #' List of prepared canopus annotations. STRING
      canopus: data/interim/annotations/example_canopusPrepared.tsv.gz

      #' List of prepared formula annotations. STRING
      formula: data/interim/annotations/example_formulaPrepared.tsv.gz

      #' List of prepared structural annotations.
      structural:
        #' Prepared GNPS structural annotations. STRING
        gnps: data/interim/annotations/example_gnpsPrepared.tsv.gz

        #' Prepared MS1 structural annotations. STRING
        ms1: data/interim/annotations/example_ms1Prepared.tsv.gz

        #' Prepared SIRIUS structural annotations. STRING
        sirius: data/interim/annotations/example_siriusPrepared.tsv.gz

        #' Prepared SPECTRAL structural annotations. STRING
        spectral: data/interim/annotations/example_spectralMatchesPrepared.tsv.gz

    #' Final results file. STRING
    processed: example_results.tsv

  #' Features files.
  features:
    #' Raw features file. STRING
    raw: data/source/example_features.csv

    #' Prepared features file. STRING
    prepared: data/interim/features/example_features.tsv.gz

  #' Libraries files.
  libraries:
    #' Structure organism pairs libraries.
    sop:
      #' Raw structure organism pairs libraries.
      raw:
        #' Closed structure organism pairs library. STRING
        closed: ../lotus-processor/data/processed/230106_closed_metadata.csv.gz

        #' ECMDB structure organism pairs library. STRING
        ecmdb: data/source/libraries/sop/ecmdb.json.zip

        #' HMDB structure organism pairs library. STRING
        hmdb: data/source/libraries/sop/hmdb/structures.zip

        #' Lotus raw structure organism pairs library. STRING
        lotus: data/source/libraries/sop/lotus.csv.gz

      #' List of prepared structure organism pairs libraries.
      prepared:
        #' Closed prepared structure organism pairs library. STRING
        closed: data/interim/libraries/sop/closed_prepared.tsv.gz

        #' ECMDB prepared structure organism pairs library. STRING
        ecmdb: data/interim/libraries/sop/ecmdb_prepared.tsv.gz

        #' HMDB prepared structure organism pairs library. STRING
        hmdb: data/interim/libraries/sop/hmdb_prepared.tsv.gz

        #' Lotus prepared structure organism pairs library. STRING
        lotus: data/interim/libraries/sop/lotus_prepared.tsv.gz

        #' RT prepared structure organism pairs library. STRING
        rt: data/interim/libraries/sop/rt_prepared.tsv.gz

        #' Spectral prepared structure organism pairs library. STRING
        spectral: data/interim/libraries/sop/spectral_prepared.tsv.gz

      #' Merged structure organism pairs library.
      merged:
        #' Merged structure organism pairs library keys. STRING
        keys: data/interim/libraries/sop/merged/keys.tsv.gz

        #' Organisms libraries.
        organisms:
          #' Organisms names. STRING
          names: data/interim/libraries/sop/merged/organisms/names.tsv.gz

          #' Organisms taxonomies.
          taxonomies:
            #' OTT organisms taxonomy. STRING
            ott: data/interim/libraries/sop/merged/organisms/taxonomies/ott.tsv.gz

        #' Structures libraries.
        structures:
          #' Structures stereo. STRING
          stereo: data/interim/libraries/sop/merged/structures/stereo.tsv.gz

          #' Structures metadata. STRING
          metadata: data/interim/libraries/sop/merged/structures/metadata.tsv.gz

          #' Structures names. STRING
          names: data/interim/libraries/sop/merged/structures/names.tsv.gz

          #' Structures taxonomies.
          taxonomies:
            #' Classyfire structures taxonomy. STRING
            cla: data/interim/libraries/sop/merged/structures/taxonomies/classyfire.tsv.gz

            #' NPClassifier structures taxonomy. STRING
            npc: data/interim/libraries/sop/merged/structures/taxonomies/npc.tsv.gz

    #' Spectral libraries. STRING
    spectral:
      #' List of negative spectral libraries. STRING
      neg:
        - data/interim/libraries/spectra/exp/internal_neg.rds
      
      #' List of positive spectral libraries. STRING
      pos:
        - data/interim/libraries/spectra/exp/internal_pos.rds

      #' List of raw spectral libraries. STRING
      raw: 
        - data/source/libraries/spectra/exp/spectral_lib_mini_with_rt.mgf

    #' Temporal libraries. STRING
    temporal:
      #' List of experimental temporal libraries.
      exp:
        #' List of experimental temporal libraries (CSV). STRING
        csv: ~

        #' List of experimental temporal libraries (MGF).
        mgf:
          #' List of negative experimental temporal libraries (MGF). STRING
          neg: [ ]

          #' List of positive experimental temporal libraries (MGF). STRING
          pos: [ ]

      #' List of in silico temporal libraries. STRING
      is:
        #' List of in silico temporal libraries (CSV). STRING
        csv: ~

        #' List of in silico temporal libraries (MGF).
        mgf:
          #' List of negative in silico temporal libraries (MGF). STRING
          neg: [ ]

          #' List of positive in silico temporal libraries (MGF). STRING
          pos: [ ]

      #' List of prepared temporal libraries. STRING
      prepared:
        - data/interim/libraries/rt/prepared.tsv.gz

  #' Metadata files.
  metadata:
    #' The path to the file containing your metadata.
    #' Must be formatted accordingly.
    #' If your experiment contains a single taxon, you can provide it below instead. STRING
    raw: data/source/example_metadata.tsv

    #' Taxonomically informed features file. STRING
    prepared: data/interim/taxa/example_taxed.tsv.gz

  #' Networks files.
  networks:
    #' Spectral networks files.
    spectral:
      #' Edges files.
      edges:
        #' Raw edges file.
        raw:
          #' Raw ms1 edges file. STRING
          ms1: data/interim/features/example_edgesMasses.tsv

          #' Raw spectral edges file. STRING
          spectral: data/interim/features/example_edgesSpectra.tsv

        #' Prepared edges file. STRING
        prepared: data/interim/features/example_edges.tsv

      #' Components files.
      components:
        #' Raw components file. STRING
        raw: data/interim/features/example_components.tsv

        #' Prepared components file. STRING
        prepared: data/interim/features/example_componentsPrepared.tsv

  #' Spectral files.
  spectral:
    #' Raw spectral file. STRING
    raw: data/source/example_spectra.mgf

#' GNPS related parameters.
gnps:
  #' GNPS job ID. STRING
  id: 41c6068e905d482db5698ad81d145d7c

  #' Workflow used within GNPS.
  #' Currently "fbmn" or "classical" supported. STRING
  workflow: fbmn

#' MS related parameters.
ms:
  #' List of adducts to be used.
  adducts:
    #' List of adducts to be used in negative. STRING
    neg:
      - "[M-H3]3-"
      - "[M-H2]2-"
      - "[M-H]-"
      - "[M+F]-"
      - "[M+Na-H2]-"
      - "[M+Cl]-"
      - "[M+K-H2]-"
      - "[M+Br]-"
      - "[2M-H]-"
      - "[3M-H]-"

    #' List of adducts to be used in positive. STRING
    pos:
      - "[M+H3]3+"
      - "[M+H2Na]3+"
      - "[M+HNa2]3+"
      - "[M+Na3]3+"
      - "[M+H2]2+"
      - "[M+HNa]2+"
      - "[M+Mg]2+"
      - "[M+HK]2+"
      - "[M+Ca]2+"
      - "[M+Na2]2+"
      - "[M+Fe]2+"
      - "[M+H]+"
      - "[M+H4N]+"
      - "[M+Na]+"
      - "[M+K]+"
      - "[M+Cu]+"
      - "[2M+Mg]2+"
      - "[2M+Ca]2+"
      - "[2M+Fe]2+"
      - "[2M+H]+"
      - "[2M+H4N]+"
      - "[2M+Na]+"
      - "[2M+K]+"

  #' List of clusters to be used.
  clusters:
    #' List of clusters to be used in negative. STRING
    neg:
      - "H2O" # (water)
      - "CH2O2" # (formic)
      - "NaCl" # (sodium chloride)
      - "C2H4O2" # (acetic)
      - "H2PO4" # (phosphoric)
      - "C2HF3O2" # (tfa)

    #' List of clusters to be used in positive. STRING
    pos:
      - "H2O" # (water)
      # - CH4O # (methanol)
      - "C2H3N" # (acetonitrile)
      # - C2H7N # (ethylamine)
      # - C2H6O # (ethanol)
      - "NaCl" # (sodium chloride)
      # - C3H8O # (isopropanol)
      # - C2H6OS # (dmso)

  #' List of neutral losses to be used. STRING
  neutral_losses:
    - "HN"
    - "CH3"
    - "O"
    - "H3N (ammonia)"
    - "H2O (water)"
    - "CHN"
    - "CO"
    - "C2H4 (2xCH2)"
    - "C2H5 (CH2-CH3)"
    - "CH2O"
    - "H5ON (H2O-H3N)"
    - "H4O2 (2xH2O)"
    - "C2H2O"
    - "CHON"
    - "CO2"
    - "CHO2"
    - "H6O3 (3xH2O)"
    - "C2O2 (2xCO)"
    - "CH6O3 (combination)"
    - "H8O4 (4xH2O)"
    - "C2H2O3 (CH2O-CO2)"
    - "C3H6O2 (CH3-CH2-COOH)"
    - "C3O3 (3xCO)"
    - "C4H9NO (combination)"
    - "C2O4 (2xCO2)"
    - "C3H4O3 (pyruvic)"
    - "C4H8O2 (butyric)"
    - "C3H7NO2 (alanine)"
    - "C3H6O3 (sugar)"
    - "H2O4S (sulfuric)"
    - "H3O4P (phosphoric)"
    - "C5H10O2 (valeric)"
    - "C3H4O4 (malonic)"
    - "C2H2O5 (CO2-CO2-H2O)"
    - "C3H8O4 (combination)"
    - "C5H9NO2 (proline)"
    - "C4O4H6 (CO2-CO2-CH3-CH3)"
    - "C4H8O4 (sugar)"
    - "C2H4O6 (CO2-CO2-H2O-H2O)"
    - "C6H6O3 (HRF)"
    - "C5H8O4 (pentose-H2O)"
    - "C8H8O2 (RDA-1)"
    - "C6H8O4 (HRF)"
    - "C9H6O2 (coumaroyl)"
    - "C6H10O4 (methylpentose/desoxyhexose-H2O)"
    - "C9H8O2 (cinnamoyl)"
    - "C7H4O4 (galloyl)"
    - "C8H8O3 (RDA-2)"
    - "C9H6O3 (caffeoyl)"
    - "C6H10O5 (hexose-H2O)"
    - "C8H8O4 (RDA-3)"
    - "C8H10O4 (RDA-2-H2O)"
    - "C6H8O6 (glucuronic-H2O)"
    - "C10H8O3 (feruloyl)"
    - "C6H13NO5 (hexose-H2N)"
    - "C6H12O6 (hexose)"
    - "C7H12O6 (quinoyl)"
    - "C6H15NO6 (hexose-H2N-H2O)"
    - "C6H14O7 (hexose-H2O)"
    - "C8H12O6 (acetylhexose-H2O)"
    - "C11H10O4 (sinapoyl)"
    - "C16H30O (pamitoyl)"
    - "C9H12O8 (malonylhexose)"
    - "C13H14O6 (benzoylhexose)"
    - "C12H20O8 (2xmethylpentose/desoxyhexose-H2O)"
    - "C15H16O7 (coumaroylhexose)"
    - "C13H14O9 (galloylhexose)"
    - "C15H16O8 (caffeoylhexose)"
    - "C12H20O10 (2xhexose-H2O)"
    - "C16H18O8 (feruloylhexose)"
    - "C17H20O9 (sinapoylhexose)"
    - "C18H30O15 (3xhexose-H2O)"

  #' Polarity used. Must be "pos" or "neg". STRING
  polarity: pos

  #' Thresholds related parameters.
  thresholds:
    #' MS2 related parameters.
    ms2:
      #' Intensity threshold for MS2. INTEGER
      intensity: 5

  #' Tolerances.
  tolerances:
    #' For mass.
    mass:
      #' Relative in ppm.
      ppm:
        #' Relative mass tolerance for MS1 in ppm. FLOAT
        ms1: 10

        #' Relative mass tolerance for MS2 in ppm. FLOAT
        ms2: 10

      #' Absolute in Dalton.
      dalton:
        #' Absolute mass tolerance for MS1 in Dalton. FLOAT
        ms1: 0.01

        #' Absolute mass tolerance for MS2 in Dalton. FLOAT
        ms2: 0.01

    #' For retention time.
    rt:
      #' Retention time tolerance for adducts in minutes. FLOAT
      adducts: 0.02

      #' Retention time tolerance for library in minutes. FLOAT
      library: 0.1

#' Names of the different variables in the input files.
names:
  #' Name of "adduct" variable in the feature table. STRING
  adduct: best ion

  #' The file(s) extension is present in the sample name. BOOLEAN
  extension: yes

  #' Name of "feature IDs" variable in the input. STRING
  features: row ID

  #' Name of "filename" variable in the input. STRING
  filename: filename

  #' Names of the prepared libraries. STRING
  libraries:
    - internal

  #' Name of "InChIKey" variable in the input. STRING
  inchikey: inchikey

  #' Name of fields present in the MGF.
  mgf:
    #' Name of "adduct" in MGF. STRING
    adduct: ~

    #' Name of "collision energy" in MGF. STRING
    collision_energy: ~

    #' Name of "compound ID" in MGF. STRING
    compound_id: FILENAME

    #' Name of "exact mass" in MGF. STRING
    exact_mass: EXACTMASS

    #' Name of "InChI" in MGF. STRING
    inchi: INCHI

    #' Name of "InChI without stereo" in MGF. STRING
    inchi_no_stereo: ~

    #' Name of "InChIKey" in MGF. STRING
    inchikey: ~

    #' Name of "InChIKey without stereo" in MGF. STRING
    inchikey_no_stereo: ~

    #' Name of "molecular formula" in MGF. STRING
    molecular_formula: ~

    #' Name of "name" in MGF. STRING
    name: NAME

    #' Name of "polarity" in MGF. STRING
    polarity: IONMODE

    #' Name of "retention time" in MGF. STRING
    retention_time: RTINSECONDS

    #' Name of "SMILES" in MGF. STRING
    smiles: SMILES

    #' Name of "SMILES without stereo" in MGF. STRING
    smiles_no_stereo: ~

    #' Name of "spectrum ID" in MGF. STRING
    spectrum_id: SPECTRUMID

    #' Name of "SPLASH" in MGF. STRING
    splash: ~

    #' Name of "synonyms" in MGF. STRING
    synonyms: ~

    #' Name of "xlogP" in MGF. STRING
    xlogp: ~

  #' Name of "precursor m/z" variable in the input. STRING
  precursor: row m/z

  #' Name of "retention time" variable.
  rt:
    #' Name of "retention time" variable in the feature table. STRING
    features: row retention time

    #' Name of "retention time" variable in the library. STRING
    library: rt

  #' Name of "SMILES" variable in the input. STRING
  smiles: smiles

  #' Name of "source IDs" variable in the input. STRING
  source: CLUSTERID1

  #' Name of "target IDs" variable in the input. STRING
  target: CLUSTERID2

  #' Name of the "taxon name" variable in the input. STRING
  taxon: ATTRIBUTE_species

#' Organisms related parameters.
organisms:
  #' Number of organisms to keep per feature. INTEGER
  candidates: 1

  #' Organisms filter related parameters.
  filter:
    #' Filter library to restrict it to a portion of organisms only. BOOLEAN
    mode: no

    #' Level at which the library will be filtered.
    #' Must be one of "domain", "phylum", "class", "order",
    #' "family", "tribe", "genus", "species", "varietas" . STRING
    level: phylum

    #' Value to be applied for filtering.
    #' "OR" can be used as "|".
    # Example: "Simaroubaceae|Gentianaceae". STRING
    value: Streptophyta

  #' OPTIONAL. If your experiment contains a single taxon, its scientific name.
  #' Else, you will need to provide a metadata file above.
  #' If you provide both, this one will have priority.
  #' Example: "Homo sapiens". STRING
  taxon: ~

#' Tools used for each step.
tools:
  #' Tool used to store metadata.
  #' Currently "gnps" or "manual" supported. STRING
  metadata: gnps

  #' Networks related parameters.
  networks:
    #' Spectral networks related parameters.
    spectral:
      #' Tool used to generate components.
      #' Currently "gnps" or "manual" supported. STRING
      components: gnps

      #' Tool used to generate edges.
      #' Currently "gnps" or "manual" supported. STRING
      edges: gnps

  #' Sirius.
  sirius:
    #' Sirius version.
    #' Currently only 5 or 6 supported. INTEGER
    version: 6

  #' Taxonomies related parameters.
  taxonomies:
    #' Biological taxonomy used for matching.
    #' Currently only "otl" supported. STRING
    biological: otl

    #' Chemical taxonomy used for matching.
    #' Currently only "npc" or supported. STRING
    chemical: npc

#' Units of the different variables in the input files.
units:
  #' Unit of the "retention time" variable in the input files. STRING
  rt: seconds

#' Weights to apply to each part of the final score.
weights:
  #' Global weights.
  global:
    #' Weight for the biological part. FLOAT
    biological: 0.500

    #' Weight for the chemical part. FLOAT
    chemical: 0.166

    #' Weight for the spectral part. FLOAT
    spectral: 0.333

  #' Weights for the biological part.
  biological:
    #' Score for a biological domain match. FLOAT
    domain: 0.10

    #' Score for a biological kingdom match. FLOAT
    kingdom: 0.20

    #' Score for a biological phylum match. FLOAT
    phylum: 0.30

    #' Score for a biological class match. FLOAT
    class: 0.40

    #' Score for a biological order match. FLOAT
    order: 0.50

    #' Score for a biological infraorder match. FLOAT
    infraorder: 0.55

    #' Score for a biological family match. FLOAT
    family: 0.60

    #' Score for a biological subfamily match. FLOAT
    subfamily: 0.65

    #' Score for a biological tribe match. FLOAT
    tribe: 0.70

    #' Score for a biological subtribe match. FLOAT
    subtribe: 0.75

    #' Score for a biological genus match. FLOAT
    genus: 0.80

    #' Score for a biological subgenus match. FLOAT
    subgenus: 0.85

    #' Score for a biological species match. FLOAT
    species: 0.90

    #' Score for a biological subspecies match. FLOAT
    subspecies: 0.95

    #' Score for a biological variety match. FLOAT
    variety: 1.00

  #' Weights for the chemical part.
  chemical:
    #' Score for a classyfire match.
    cla:
      #' Score for a chemical kingdom match. FLOAT
      kingdom: 0.25

      #' Score for a chemical superclass match. FLOAT
      superclass: 0.50

      #' Score for a chemical class match. FLOAT
      class: 0.75

      #' Score for a chemical parent match. FLOAT
      parent: 1.00

    #' Score for a NPClassifier match.
    npc:
      #' Score for a chemical kingdom match. FLOAT
      pathway: 0.333

      #' Score for a chemical superclass match. FLOAT
      superclass: 0.666

      #' Score for a chemical class match. FLOAT
      class: 1.000

#' Options.
options:
  #' Report compounds names. Can be very large. BOOLEAN
  compounds_names: no

  #' Do not use it. BOOLEAN
  force: no

  #' Filter high confidence candidates only. BOOLEAN
  high_confidence: yes

  #' Remove ties. BOOLEAN
  remove_ties: no

  #' Summarise results to one row per feature. BOOLEAN
  summarise: no

name: paths.yaml
content:
---
base_dir: ./
data:
  path: data
  interim:
    path: data/interim
    annotations:
      path: data/interim/annotations
      example_sirius:
        v5: data/interim/annotations/example_sirius_5.zip
        v6: data/interim/annotations/example_sirius_6.zip
    features:
      path: data/interim/features
    libraries:
      path: data/interim/libraries
      adducts:
        path: data/interim/libraries/adducts
        neg: data/interim/libraries/adducts/neg.tsv.gz
        pos: data/interim/libraries/adducts/pos.tsv.gz
      sop:
        path: data/interim/libraries/sop
        closed: data/interim/libraries/sop/closed_prepared.tsv.gz
        hmdb: data/interim/libraries/sop/hmdb_prepared.tsv.gz
        hmdb_minimal: data/interim/libraries/sop/hmdb_minimal.tsv.gz
        lotus: data/interim/libraries/sop/lotus_prepared.tsv.gz
        merged:
          path: data/interim/libraries/sop/merged
          keys: data/interim/libraries/sop/merged/keys.tsv.gz
          organisms:
            path: data/interim/libraries/sop/merged/organisms
            names: data/interim/libraries/sop/merged/organisms/names.tsv.gz
            taxonomies:
              path: data/interim/libraries/sop/merged/organisms/taxonomies
              ott: data/interim/libraries/sop/merged/organisms/taxonomies/ott.tsv.gz
          structures:
            path: data/interim/libraries/sop/merged/structures
            stereo: data/interim/libraries/sop/merged/structures/stereo.tsv.gz
            metadata: data/interim/libraries/sop/merged/structures/metadata.tsv.gz
            names: data/interim/libraries/sop/merged/structures/names.tsv.gz
            taxonomies:
              path: data/interim/libraries/sop/merged/structures/taxonomies
              cla: data/interim/libraries/sop/merged/structures/taxonomies/classyfire.tsv.gz
              npc: data/interim/libraries/sop/merged/structures/taxonomies/npc.tsv.gz
      spectra:
        path: data/interim/libraries/spectra
        exp:
          path: data/interim/libraries/spectra/exp
          mona:
            pos: data/interim/libraries/spectra/exp/mona_pos.rds
            neg: data/interim/libraries/spectra/exp/mona_neg.rds
        is:
          path: data/interim/libraries/spectra/is
          hmdb:
            pos: data/interim/libraries/spectra/is/hmdb_pos.rds
            neg: data/interim/libraries/spectra/is/hmdb_neg.rds
          lotus:
            pos: data/interim/libraries/spectra/is/lotus_pos.rds
            neg: data/interim/libraries/spectra/is/lotus_neg.rds
    params:
      path: data/interim/params
    taxa:
      path: data/interim/taxa
  processed:
    path: data/processed
  source:
    path: data/source
    features: data/source/example_features.csv
    metadata: data/source/example_metadata.tsv
    spectra: data/source/example_spectra.mgf
    benchmark:
      path: data/source/benchmark
      cleaned: data/interim/benchmark/cleaned_libraries_matchms/results_library_cleaning/cleaned_spectra.mgf
      mgf:
        neg: data/interim/benchmark/benchmark_neg.mgf
        pos: data/interim/benchmark/benchmark_pos.mgf
      zip: data/source/benchmark/cleaned_libraries_matchms.zip
    libraries:
      path: data/source/libraries
      rt:
        path: data/source/libraries/rt
        example_mini: data/source/libraries/rt/example_lib_mini_rt.tsv
      sop:
        path: data/source/libraries/sop

name: scripts/annotate_masses.R
content:
start <- Sys.time()

library(tima)

log_debug(
  "This script",
  crayon::green("annotates based on exact mass (MS1)")
)
log_debug("Authors: ", crayon::green("AR"), "\n")
log_debug("Contributors: ", crayon::blue("CH"), crayon::cyan("MS"), "\n")

targets::tar_make(names = tidyselect::matches("^ann_ms1_pre"))

end <- Sys.time()

log_debug("Script finished in", crayon::green(format(end - start)))

name: scripts/annotate_spectra.R
content:
start <- Sys.time()

library(tima)

log_debug(
  "This script",
  crayon::green(
    "performs spectral similarity calculation",
    "to annotate against a spectral library. \n"
  )
)
log_debug("Authors: ", crayon::green("AR"), "\n")
log_debug("Contributors: ...")

targets::tar_make(names = tidyselect::matches("^ann_spe_pre"))

end <- Sys.time()

log_debug("Script finished in", crayon::green(format(end - start)))

name: scripts/change_tests.R
content:
paths <- yaml::read_yaml(file = system.file("paths.yaml", package = "tima"))

paths$tests$mode <- "yes"
paths$urls$examples$spectra <- paths$urls$examples$spectra_mini

yaml::write_yaml(
  x = paths,
  file = system.file("paths.yaml", package = "tima")
)

name: scripts/docopt/annotate_masses.txt

You can use this script with the following example:

Usage:
  annotate_masses.R [--fil-ann-pre-str=<fil-ann-pre-str>] [--fil-lib-sop-mer=<fil-lib-sop-mer>] [--fil-lib-add-neg=<fil-lib-add-neg>] [--fil-lib-add-pos=<fil-lib-add-pos>] [--fil-lib-add-pro=<fil-lib-add-pro>] [--ms-add-neg=<ms-add-neg>] [--ms-add-pos=<ms-add-pos>] [--ms-clu-neg=<ms-clu-neg>] [--ms-clu-pos=<ms-clu-pos>] [--ms-neu=<ms-neu>] [--ms-pol=<ms-pol>] [--ms-tol-mas-ppm-ms1=<ms-tol-mas-ppm-ms1>] [--ms-tol-mas-dal-ms1=<ms-tol-mas-dal-ms1>] [--ms-tol-rt-add=<ms-tol-rt-add>] [--force=<force>]

Arguments:
  fil-ann-pre-str            List of prepared structural annotations. STRING
  fil-fea-pre                Prepared features file. STRING
  fil-lib-add-neg            Negative adducts. STRING
  fil-lib-add-pos            Positive adducts. STRING

  fil-lib-sop-mer            Merged structure organism pairs library. STRING

  ms-add-pos                 List of adducts to be used in positive. STRING
  ms-clu-neg                 List of clusters to be used in negative. STRING
  ms-clu-pos                 List of clusters to be used in positive. STRING
  ms-neu                     List of neutral losses to be used. STRING
  ms-pol                     Polarity used. Must be "pos" or "neg". STRING
  ms-tol-mas-ppm-ms1         Relative mass tolerance for MS1 in ppm. FLOAT
  ms-tol-mas-dal-ms1         Absolute mass tolerance for MS1 in Dalton. FLOAT
  ms-tol-rt-add              Retention time tolerance for adducts in minutes. FLOAT

  names-mgf-po               Name of "polarity" in MGF. STRING

  names-mgf-si               Name of "spectrum ID" in MGF. STRING

name: scripts/docopt/prepare_params.txt
content:
You can use this script with the following example:
  Rscript inst/scripts/prepare_params.R

Usage:
  prepare_params.R  [--fil-pat=<fil-pat>] [--gnps-id=<gnps-id>] [--gnps-workflow=<gnps-workflow>] [--ms-pol=<ms-pol>] [--org-tax=<org-tax>]

Arguments:
  fil-pat                    Pattern to identify the files. STRING
  gnps-id                    GNPS job ID. STRING
  gnps-workflow              Workflow used within GNPS. Currently "fbmn" or "classical" supported. STRING
  ms-pol                     Polarity used. Must be "pos" or "neg". STRING
  org-tax                    OPTIONAL. Force all features to be attributed to given taxon. Example: "Homo sapiens". STRING

Options:
  -h --help                  Shows this screen.
  -v --version               Shows version.

name: scripts/docopt/prepare_taxa.txt
content:
You can use this script with the following example:
  Rscript inst/scripts/prepare_taxa.R --fil-met-pre data/interim/taxa/example_taxed.tsv.gz --org-can 1 --names-extension TRUE --names-features "row ID" --names-filename filename --names-taxon ATTRIBUTE_species

Usage:
  prepare_taxa.R [--fil-fea-raw=<fil-fea-raw>] [--fil-met-raw=<fil-met-raw>] [--fil-met-pre=<fil-met-pre>] [--gnps-id=<gnps-id>] [--names-extension=<names-extension>] [--names-features=<names-features>] [--names-filename=<names-filename>] [--names-taxon=<names-taxon>] [--org-can=<org-can>] [--org-tax=<org-tax>] [--too-met=<too-met>]

Arguments:
  fil-fea-raw                Raw features file. STRING
  fil-met-raw                OPTIONAL. If tool is "manual". Biological origin metadata file. STRING
  fil-met-pre                Taxonomically informed features file. STRING

  names-extension            The file(s) extension is present in the sample name. BOOLEAN
  names-features             Name of "feature IDs" variable in the input. STRING
  names-filename             Name of "filename" variable in the input. STRING
  names-taxon                Name of the "taxon name" variable in the input. STRING

  org-can                    Number of organisms to keep per feature. INTEGER
  org-tax                    OPTIONAL. Force all features to be attributed to given taxon. Example: "Homo sapiens". STRING

Options:
  -h --help                  Shows this screen.
  -v --version               Shows version.

name: scripts/docopt/weight_annotations.txt
content:
You can use this script with the following example:
  Rscript inst/scripts/weight_annotations.R

Usage:
  weight_annotations.R [--ann-can-fin=<ann-can-fin>] [--ann-ms1only=<ann-ms1only>] [--ann-thr-ms1-bio=<ann-thr-ms1-bio>] [--ann-thr-ms1-che=<ann-thr-ms1-che>] [--ann-thr-ms1-con=<ann-thr-ms1-con>] [--ann-thr-con=<ann-thr-con>] [--fil-ann-fil=<fil-ann-fil>] [--fil-ann-pre-can=<fil-ann-pre-can>] [--fil-ann-pre-for=<fil-ann-pre-for>] [--fil-ann-pro=<fil-ann-pro>] [--fil-lib-sop-mer=<fil-lib-sop-mer>] [--fil-net-spe-edg-pre=<fil-net-spe-edg-pre>] [--fil-met-pre=<fil-met-pre>] [--wei-glo-bio=<wei-glo-bio>] [--wei-glo-che=<wei-glo-che>] [--wei-glo-spe=<wei-glo-spe>] [--wei-bio-01=<wei-bio-01>] [--wei-bio-02=<wei-bio-02>] [--wei-bio-03=<wei-bio-03>] [--wei-bio-04=<wei-bio-04>] [--wei-bio-05=<wei-bio-05>] [--wei-bio-06=<wei-bio-06>] [--wei-bio-07=<wei-bio-07>] [--wei-bio-08=<wei-bio-08>] [--wei-bio-09=<wei-bio-09>] [--wei-bio-10=<wei-bio-10>] [--wei-bio-11=<wei-bio-11>] [--wei-bio-12=<wei-bio-12>] [--wei-bio-13=<wei-bio-13>] [--wei-bio-14=<wei-bio-14>] [--wei-bio-15=<wei-bio-15>] [--wei-che-11=<wei-che-11>] [--wei-che-12=<wei-che-12>] [--wei-che-13=<wei-che-13>]  [--wei-che-14=<wei-che-14>] [--wei-che-21=<wei-che-21>] [--wei-che-22=<wei-che-22>] [--wei-che-23=<wei-che-23>] [--compounds-names=<compounds-names>] [--high-confidence=<high-confidence>] [--remove-ties=<remove-ties>] [--summarise=<summarise>] [--force=<force>]

Arguments:
  ann-can-fin                Number of final candidates. INTEGER
  ann-ms1only                Erase MS2 results and keep MS1 only. BOOLEAN
  ann-thr-ms1-bio            Minimal biological score to keep MS1 only annotation. FLOAT
  ann-thr-ms1-che            Minimal chemical score to keep MS1 only annotation. FLOAT
  ann-thr-ms1-con            Condition to be used to retain candidates. Must be "OR" or "AND". Example: Minimum 0.5 biological AND 0.5 chemical. STRING
  ann-thr-con                Minimal consistency score (chemical) to consider a class. FLOAT

  fil-ann-fil                Filtered annotation file. STRING
  fil-ann-pre-can            List of prepared canopus annotations. STRING
  fil-ann-pre-for            List of prepared formula annotations. STRING
  fil-ann-pro                Final results file. STRING
  fil-lib-sop-mer            Merged structure organism pairs library. STRING
  fil-net-spe-edg-pre        Prepared edges file. STRING
  fil-met-pre                Taxonomically informed features file. STRING

  wei-glo-bio                Weight for the biological part. FLOAT
  wei-glo-che                Weight for the chemical part. FLOAT
  wei-glo-spe                Weight for the spectral part. FLOAT

  wei-bio-01                 Score for a biological domain match. FLOAT
  wei-bio-02                 Score for a biological kingdom match. FLOAT
  wei-bio-03                 Score for a biological phylum match. FLOAT
  wei-bio-04                 Score for a biological class match. FLOAT
  wei-bio-05                 Score for a biological order match. FLOAT
  wei-bio-06                 Score for a biological infraorder match. FLOAT
  wei-bio-07                 Score for a biological family match. FLOAT
  wei-bio-08                 Score for a biological subfamily match. FLOAT
  wei-bio-09                 Score for a biological tribe match. FLOAT
  wei-bio-10                 Score for a biological subtribe match. FLOAT
  wei-bio-11                 Score for a biological genus match. FLOAT
  wei-bio-12                 Score for a biological subgenus match. FLOAT
  wei-bio-13                 Score for a biological species match. FLOAT
  wei-bio-14                 Score for a biological subspecies match. FLOAT
  wei-bio-15                 Score for a biological variety match. FLOAT

  wei-che-11                 Score for a chemical classyfire kingdom match. FLOAT
  wei-che-12                 Score for a chemical classyfire superclass match. FLOAT
  wei-che-13                 Score for a chemical classyfire class match. FLOAT
  wei-che-14                 Score for a chemical classyfire parent match. FLOAT
  wei-che-21                 Score for a chemical NPC pathway match. FLOAT
  wei-che-22                 Score for a chemical NPC superclass match. FLOAT
  wei-che-23                 Score for a chemical NPC class match. FLOAT

  compounds-names            Report compounds names. Can be very large. BOOLEAN
  force                      Do not use it. BOOLEAN
  high-confidence            Report high confidence candidates only. BOOLEAN
  remove-ties                Remove ties. BOOLEAN
  summarise                  Summarize results (1 row per feature). BOOLEAN

Options:
  -h --help                  Shows this screen.
  -v --version               Shows version.
